= ⬡ QUARTER III GATHERING — The Red Work Approaches

*Theme:* Peer review of Adept-level mineral preparations; collective witnessing of the long work.

#hm-note[
  This is the most substantive gathering of Year Three. Allocate enough time for
  each student to present their full mineral work without rushing. The collective
  witnessing of the long work — each student naming what is in each sealed vessel,
  how long it has been sealed, and what they observe — is itself an operative
  contribution to each preparation's development.
]

*Students bring:*
- Their mineral preparations in current state: full presentation of all active works —
  name, contents, age, current colour stage, and observations.
- Their personal alchemical journal across all three years (one passage read aloud
  — chosen by the student, not assigned).
- The finalised letter to a future Tyro.
- A declaration (in whatever current form) of what they will carry forward from
  this curriculum into their own practice.

